With Real Madrid clinching the La Liga on Saturday after defeating Espanyol 4-0 at the Santiago Bernabeu, Real Madrid coach, Carlo Ancelotti became the first manager to lift trophies in the top five European leagues.
The Italian professional football manager had already won the league with AC Milan in Italy, Chelsea in England, Paris Saint-Germain in France, Bayern Munich in Germany and on Saturday afternoon he won with Real Madrid in Spain.
Carlo Ancelotti becoming the first manager to win all of Europe’s top five leagues after his side, Real Madrid recently beat Espanyol 4-0 on Saturday has attracted reactions from football fans, as some have called him a quiet coach with great records, while some have congratulated Carlo Ancelotti.
